ifically with respect to the Directive 2013/59/Euratom in all sectors where ionising radiation are applied. To reflect the RPE training scheme, six chapters have been developed in this textbook: Radioactivity and nuclear physics Interaction of ionising radiation with matter Dosimetry Biological effects of ionising radiation Detection and measurement of ionising radiation Uses of sources of ionising radiation The result is a homogeneous textbook, dealing with the ERPTS learning outcomes suggested by ENETRAPII project (European Network on Education and Training in RAdiological Protection II) from the 7th Framework Programme. The production of this first module “basics” training material, in the form of a textbook as learning tool, will contribute to facilitate mutual recognition and enhanced mobility of these professionals across the European Union.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aRadiopharmaceuticals. 4aRadioprotection. 7aSCIENCE / Radiation.2bisacsh1 aAmmerich, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBodineau, Jean-Christophe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruchet, Hugues, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEtard, Cécile, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJimonet, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJimonet, Christine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMassiot, Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMassiot, Philippe, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoreau, Jean-Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMétivier, Henri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/c